should board at Platform 5.

249
00:15:37,479 --> 00:15:38,605
Boarding for the

250
00:15:38,606 --> 00:15:40,440
Mito line
will be at Platform 15.
Attention, all passengers.

251
00:15:40,441 --> 00:15:46,071
The Ryomo line has been
delayed by heavy snowfall.

252
00:15:46,614 --> 00:15:50,366
We apologize for any
potential inconvenience,

253
00:15:50,367 --> 00:15:53,913
and request your patience and
understanding until the train arrives.

254
00:15:54,580 --> 00:15:55,622
The next train

255
00:15:55,623 --> 00:15:59,417
I had no choice but to make my way
bound for Takasaki
is expected to depart at 8:15 PM.

256
00:15:59,418 --> 00:16:01,295
To the station where
Akari was waiting.

257
00:16:55,474 --> 00:17:00,478
The Ashikaga-Maebashi train bound for
Takasaki is now arriving at Platform 8.

258
00:17:00,479 --> 00:17:02,439
Please remain behind the line.

259
00:17:34,513 --> 00:17:36,556
Attention, all passengers.

260
00:17:36,557 --> 00:17:41,602
This train will be stopping due to
delays caused by the snow.

261
00:17:41,603 --> 00:17:44,105
We apologize for any inconvenience.

262
00:17:44,106 --> 00:17:47,026
We are presently unable to determine
when service will resume.

263
00:17:47,484 --> 00:17:49,152
Again.

264
00:17:49,153 --> 00:17:53,614
The train will be stopping due to
scheduling delays caused by the snow.

265
00:17:53,615 --> 00:17:55,783
We apologize for any inconvenience.

266
00:17:55,784 --> 00:17:58,704
We are presently unable to determine
when service will resume.

267
00:18:03,125 --> 00:18:04,208
Dear Takaki,

268
00:18:04,209 --> 00:18:05,335
How are you doing?

269
00:18:06,462 --> 00:18:08,254
I have to wake up early for my club,

270
00:18:08,255 --> 00:18:10,673
so I'm writing this letter on the train.

271
00:18:10,674 --> 00:18:13,176
When I read Akari's letters,

272
00:18:13,177 --> 00:18:16,138
for some reason I always
pictured her alone.

273
00:18:19,683 --> 00:18:22,143
The train ended up parked out there,

274
00:18:22,144 --> 00:18:25,689
in the middle of nowhere,
for two more hours.

275
00:18:26,690 --> 00:18:29,526
Each minute felt like an eternity...

276
00:18:30,235 --> 00:18:33,321
I could sense hovering malice...

277
00:18:33,322 --> 00:18:35,657
...as time slowly crept by.

278
00:18:37,117 --> 00:18:39,786
But I could only grit my teeth...

279
00:18:39,787 --> 00:18:44,291
...and choke back my tears.

280
00:18:46,251 --> 00:18:47,251
Akari...

281
00:18:48,504 --> 00:18:49,629
I hope that...

282
00:18:49,630 --> 00:18:52,091
...you already...

283
00:18:54,384 --> 00:18:56,762
...went home.

284
00:19:11,110 --> 00:19:16,198
The Ashikaga-Maebashi train bound for
Takasaki is now arriving at Platform 3.

285
00:19:18,158 --> 00:19:21,370
This train will be stopping here
briefly due to a snow delay.

286
00:19:58,532 --> 00:19:59,533
Akari...

287
00:20:29,563 --> 00:20:30,856
It's so good.

288
00:20:31,565 --> 00:20:32,565
Really?

289
00:20:32,566 --> 00:20:34,358
It's just roasted green tea.

290
00:20:34,359 --> 00:20:35,359
Roasted green tea?

291
00:20:35,861 --> 00:20:37,361
Never had it.

292
00:20:37,362 --> 00:20:37,863
Liar.

293
00:20:37,864 --> 00:20:39,780
I guarantee that you have.

294
00:20:39,781 --> 00:20:40,657
You sure?

295
00:20:40,657 --> 00:20:41,657
Yep.

296
00:20:42,618 --> 00:20:44,535
And, here.

297
00:20:44,536 --> 00:20:48,080
I made it myself, so I can't
vouch for the taste...

298
00:20:48,081 --> 00:20:50,416
But you can try it, if you want.

299
00:20:50,417 --> 00:20:51,710
Thank you.

300
00:20:52,878 --> 00:20:55,339
I'm starving.

301
00:20:58,717 --> 00:20:59,717
How is it?

302
00:21:03,847 --> 00:21:07,350
The best food I've ever tasted in my life.

303
00:21:07,351 --> 00:21:08,559
Gimme a break.

304
00:21:08,560 --> 00:21:09,685
I'm serious.

305
00:21:09,686 --> 00:21:11,479
It's just because you're hungry.

306
00:21:11,480 --> 00:21:12,563
You sure?

307
00:21:12,564 --> 00:21:13,606
Yep.

308
00:21:13,607 --> 00:21:15,234
But I'll have some too.

309
00:21:20,405 --> 00:21:22,698
You're moving soon, right?

310
00:21:22,699 --> 00:21:24,325
Yeah, next week.

311
00:21:24,326 --> 00:21:25,910
Kagoshima, huh?

312
00:21:25,911 --> 00:21:26,745
It's pretty far away.

313
00:21:26,745 --> 00:21:27,745
Yeah.

314
00:21:28,747 --> 00:21:30,915
Same goes for Tochigi, though.

315
00:21:30,916 --> 00:21:32,793
You're stranded out here now.

316
00:21:36,046 --> 00:21:37,797
We'll be closing up soon.

317
00:21:37,798 --> 00:21:40,383
- There won't be any
more trains coming in.
- Oh, okay.

318
00:21:40,384 --> 00:21:42,593
It's snowing hard. You kids be careful.

319
00:21:42,594 --> 00:21:43,594
We will.

320
00:22:07,119 --> 00:22:09,453
Look, there's the tree.

321
00:22:09,454 --> 00:22:11,122
The one you mentioned in your letter?

322
00:22:11,123 --> 00:22:12,958
Yeah, the cherry tree.

323
00:22:20,465 --> 00:22:21,465
Say...

324
00:22:22,509 --> 00:22:24,636
Doesn't it remind you of snow?

325
00:22:32,811 --> 00:22:33,811
Yeah, it does.

326
00:22:44,114 --> 00:22:45,449
In that moment,

327
00:22:46,658 --> 00:22:51,913
I think I realized where eternity,
the heart, and the soul, truly exist.

328
00:22:52,664 --> 00:22:57,043
It was like I was sharing every experience
from my thirteen years on this planet.

329
00:22:57,044 --> 00:22:59,671
But then, in the next moment...

330
00:23:00,380 --> 00:23:02,549
...I felt unbearably sad.

331
00:23:04,885 --> 00:23:09,848
What was I supposed to do with
Akari's warmth, her soul?

332
00:23:12,684 --> 00:23:14,853
I didn't know the answer.

333
00:23:18,023 --> 00:23:21,692
And that was when it became clear to me...

334
00:23:21,693 --> 00:23:24,528
...that we wouldn't always be together.

335
00:23:24,529 --> 00:23:29,493
We still had our entire
lives before us.

336
00:23:29,785 --> 00:23:32,371
So much time left...

337
00:23:34,998 --> 00:23:38,959
But soon enough,

338
00:23:38,960 --> 00:23:41,587
my worries melted away,

339
00:23:41,588 --> 00:23:46,009
leaving only the sensation
of Akari's soft lips on mine.

340
00:24:04,069 --> 00:24:06,904
We spent that night...

341
00:24:06,905 --> 00:24:09,699
...in a small shed on the
outskirts of a farm.

342
00:24:11,118 --> 00:24:12,868
We wrapped ourselves
up in an old blanket...

343
00:24:12,869 --> 00:24:15,121
...and talked away the hours...

344
00:24:15,122 --> 00:24:17,749
...until we finally fell asleep.

345
00:24:18,792 --> 00:24:22,211
In the morning,
the trains were running again,

346
00:24:22,212 --> 00:24:24,506
and we said our goodbyes.

347
00:24:27,884 --> 00:24:28,968
Um...

348
00:24:28,969 --> 00:24:29,969
Takaki.

349
00:24:32,055 --> 00:24:33,682
Takaki...

350
00:24:34,850 --> 00:24:37,768
I know you'll be just fine.

351
00:24:37,769 --> 00:24:38,894
I know it!

352
00:24:38,895 --> 00:24:39,938
Thanks...

353
00:24:41,481 --> 00:24:42,691
Take care of yourself, Akari!

354
00:24:43,567 --> 00:24:44,650
I'll write!

355
00:24:44,651 --> 00:24:45,651
And call!

356
00:24:58,748 --> 00:25:03,670
I never told Akari
about the letter I lost.

357
00:25:05,380 --> 00:25:08,008
To Takaki Tono
Because a single kiss...

358
00:25:08,633 --> 00:25:13,013
...was enough to make me feel
like my whole world had changed.

359
00:25:20,812 --> 00:25:25,150
I longed for the ability to take
care of her, to keep her safe.

360
00:25:25,984 --> 00:25:29,778
And as thoughts of
her consumed me,

361
00:25:29,779 --> 00:25:33,200
I proceeded to stare
out the window.

362
00:25:33,909 --> 00:25:36,703
Episode 1 - Tale of Cherry Blossoms
End

363
00:25:55,514 --> 00:25:57,182
Episode 2

364
00:27:01,955 --> 00:27:04,123
Kanae, are you going back
there after school?

365
00:27:04,124 --> 00:27:04,833
Yup.

366
00:27:04,834 --> 00:27:05,916
That okay with you?

367
00:27:05,917 --> 00:27:06,459
Sure.

368
00:27:06,460 --> 00:27:08,377
But don't forget to study.

369
00:27:08,378 --> 00:27:09,378
I won't!

370
00:27:39,909 --> 00:27:40,909
Okay.

371
00:27:55,342 --> 00:27:56,342
Morning.

372
00:27:56,926 --> 00:27:58,636
Good morning, Takaki.

373
00:27:58,637 --> 00:28:00,012
You're sure here early.

374
00:28:00,013 --> 00:28:01,138
So are you.

375
00:28:01,139 --> 00:28:02,431
I'm guessing you went
down to the beach?

376
00:28:02,432 --> 00:28:03,557
Yup.

377
00:28:03,558 --> 00:28:04,558
You're so dedicated.

378
00:28:06,478 --> 00:28:07,854
Not really...

379
00:28:09,105 --> 00:28:10,648
See you later, Takaki.

380
00:28:10,649 --> 00:28:11,733
Right.

381
00:28:14,069 --> 00:28:14,903
Listen up.

382
00:28:14,904 --> 00:28:16,654
It's decision-making time, folks.

383
00:28:16,655 --> 00:28:18,947
This is due on Monday.

384
00:28:18,948 --> 00:28:21,368
Make sure you discuss
it with your parents.

385
00:28:21,951 --> 00:28:23,744
Career Plan

386
00:28:23,745 --> 00:28:26,247
Sasaki's going to college in Tokyo.

387
00:28:26,581 --> 00:28:27,706
Wow...

388
00:28:27,707 --> 00:28:30,084
I'm shooting for a junior
college in Kumamoto.

389
00:28:30,085 --> 00:28:31,460
What about you, Kanae?

390
00:28:31,461 --> 00:28:32,379
Huh?

391
00:28:32,380 --> 00:28:33,504
Um...

392
00:28:33,505 --> 00:28:35,089
You gonna look for a job?

393
00:28:35,090 --> 00:28:36,216
Um...

394
00:28:36,549 --> 00:28:39,259
You don't think about
anything, do you?

395
00:28:39,260 --> 00:28:40,969
Except your precious Takaki.

396
00:28:40,970 --> 00:28:43,263
I bet he has a girlfriend
back in Tokyo.

397
00:28:43,264 --> 00:28:44,307
Don't say that!

398
00:29:12,085 --> 00:29:13,711
Still having trouble?

399
00:29:13,712 --> 00:29:16,214
Yeah, I don't know what
I'm doing wrong.

400
00:29:17,006 --> 00:29:19,174
Don't stress about it too much.

401
00:29:19,175 --> 00:29:21,093
You'll be back on the waves
before you know it.

402
00:29:21,094 --> 00:29:23,262
I wish I had your positive attitude.

403
00:29:23,263 --> 00:29:25,098
What's the rush?

404
00:29:26,933 --> 00:29:29,894
The way things are going, I won't have
time to tell him before we graduate.

405
00:29:49,414 --> 00:29:51,081
Thanks, sis.

406
00:29:51,082 --> 00:29:52,166
I can take you home.

407
00:29:52,167 --> 00:29:54,252
It's okay. I'll go on my Cub.

408
00:30:21,362 --> 00:30:22,654
Oh, Kanae.

409
00:30:22,655 --> 00:30:23,573
You heading home now?

410
00:30:23,574 --> 00:30:26,033
Yep. And you?

411
00:30:26,034 --> 00:30:27,201
Yeah.

412
00:30:27,202 --> 00:30:28,328
Wanna go together?

413
00:30:29,537 --> 00:30:32,165
If I had a tail like a dog's,

414
00:30:32,540 --> 00:30:36,461
it would've wagged so hard,
my glee would've been plain as day.

415
00:30:38,296 --> 00:30:42,508
But my sigh of relief over
not being a dog...

416
00:30:42,509 --> 00:30:46,470
...was also a sigh of disgust
at how stupid I sounded.

417
00:30:46,471 --> 00:30:47,554
Despite all that,

418
00:30:47,555 --> 00:30:50,642
I was overjoyed to be
riding home with Takaki.

419
00:30:53,603 --> 00:30:54,770
From the moment I met him,

420
00:30:54,771 --> 00:30:56,355
2nd Year, Class 1
I could tell Takaki was

421
00:30:56,356 --> 00:30:59,483
This is Takaki Tono from Tokyo.
Please introduce yourself.
somehow different from the other boys.

422
00:30:59,484 --> 00:31:00,484
Takaki Tono

423
00:31:00,485 --> 00:31:02,027
I'm Takaki Tono.

424
00:31:02,028 --> 00:31:04,571
I'm used to moving around
because of my parents' jobs,

425
00:31:04,572 --> 00:31:06,782
but I'm not used to living
on this island yet.

426
00:31:06,783 --> 00:31:08,325
I hope to get to know everyone.

427
00:31:08,326 --> 00:31:10,661
I fell in love with him the
day he came to our school.

428
00:31:10,662 --> 00:31:12,996
I wanted to go to the same
high school as him...

429
00:31:12,997 --> 00:31:16,458
Okay, let's move on to the next request.
...so I worked my butt off to get accepted.

430
00:31:16,459 --> 00:31:18,001
Every time I saw him,

431
00:31:18,002 --> 00:31:22,005
- There's nothing to do out here.
- It's still better than Tokyo.
I fell deeper in love.

432
00:31:22,006 --> 00:31:23,382
I was so scared...

433
00:31:23,383 --> 00:31:25,175
And every day hurt...

434
00:31:25,176 --> 00:31:27,427
But I was so happy
whenever I saw him...

435
00:31:27,428 --> 00:31:29,639
I couldn't help myself.

436
00:31:31,808 --> 00:31:34,518
You're so predictable.

437
00:31:34,519 --> 00:31:35,603
I love the way it tastes.

438
00:31:36,312 --> 00:31:39,565
You're always so sincere.

439
00:31:39,566 --> 00:31:40,566
Yeah.

440
00:31:43,069 --> 00:31:44,070
I'll wait outside.

441
00:31:44,696 --> 00:31:46,196
Okay...

442
00:31:46,197 --> 00:31:47,322
Just this, please.

443
00:31:47,323 --> 00:31:49,199
That'll be ninety yen.

444
00:31:49,200 --> 00:31:50,118
Here you go.

445
00:31:50,119 --> 00:31:51,202
Thanks for shopping here.

446
00:32:02,213 --> 00:32:03,297
Welcome back.

447
00:32:03,298 --> 00:32:04,257
What'd you get?

448
00:32:04,257 --> 00:32:05,174
Well...

449
00:32:05,175 --> 00:32:09,238
I thought about it, and decided
to stick with this yogurt drink.
I would spot Takaki texting
someone from time to time.

450
00:32:09,262 --> 00:32:10,888
And every single time,

451
00:32:10,889 --> 00:32:14,641
Guard Earth from Space
I'd wish that it was me.

452
00:32:14,642 --> 00:32:18,271
I just couldn't help myself.

453
00:32:28,072 --> 00:32:29,406
Hi, Cub! I'm home!

454
00:32:29,407 --> 00:32:32,327
That's right, Cubbie... I'm back.

455
00:32:52,847 --> 00:32:55,265
We have an announcement
from the town council.

456
00:32:55,266 --> 00:32:58,435
Sakai's will be the next gas
station on weekend duty.

457
00:32:58,436 --> 00:33:01,104
Kanae Sumida from Class 3-1,

458
00:33:01,105 --> 00:33:02,814
Mr. Ito would like to see you.

459
00:33:02,815 --> 00:33:04,107
Please report to the guidance

460
00:33:04,108 --> 00:33:05,788
counselor's office.
That's your girlfriend.

461
00:33:06,110 --> 00:33:07,486
She's not my girlfriend.

462
00:33:07,487 --> 00:33:11,323
Career Plan - Kanae Sumida

463
00:33:11,324 --> 00:33:13,784
You're the only one who
hasn't turned one in.

464
00:33:13,785 --> 00:33:15,285
I'm sorry.

465
00:33:15,286 --> 00:33:16,662
Now look here.

466
00:33:16,663 --> 00:33:18,163
I probably shouldn't say this,

467
00:33:18,164 --> 00:33:20,791
but you don't need to worry
so much about it.

468
00:33:20,792 --> 00:33:22,834
Has Ms. Sumida suggested anything?

469
00:33:22,835 --> 00:33:23,835
No.

470
00:33:26,839 --> 00:33:28,548
If you can't make up your mind,

471
00:33:28,549 --> 00:33:30,801
you could always go to an
in-prefecture junior college.

472
00:33:30,802 --> 00:33:31,802
But...

473
00:33:33,680 --> 00:33:35,682
My sister has nothing
to do with this.

474
00:33:53,700 --> 00:33:54,700
I mean...

475
00:33:56,577 --> 00:33:59,788
I can't even surf, after
I begged her to teach me...

476
00:33:59,789 --> 00:34:02,624
I can't tell the boy
I like how I feel...

477
00:34:02,625 --> 00:34:06,045
I can't do anything...

478
00:34:31,404 --> 00:34:33,196
Thanks for shopping here.

479
00:34:33,197 --> 00:34:34,531
Oh, you're welcome.

480
00:34:34,532 --> 00:34:35,658
Bye.

481
00:35:04,228 --> 00:35:06,563
Whenever I was around Takaki,

482
00:35:06,564 --> 00:35:10,234
I would get a pain in my chest.

483
00:35:10,943 --> 00:35:12,402
Takaki.

484
00:35:12,403 --> 00:35:13,403
Kanae?

485
00:35:13,404 --> 00:35:14,280
What's up?

486
00:35:14,280 --> 00:35:15,280
How'd you find me?

487
00:35:16,365 --> 00:35:20,243
I saw your scooter, so I stopped.
Do you mind?

488
00:35:20,244 --> 00:35:21,578
Nah, it's fine.

489
00:35:21,579 --> 00:35:22,913
I'm happy to see you.

490
00:35:22,914 --> 00:35:25,582
I missed you in the
parking lot today.

491
00:35:25,583 --> 00:35:26,875
Same here.

492
00:35:26,876 --> 00:35:28,419
He's so nice.

493
00:35:29,337 --> 00:35:32,423
So nice it sometimes
makes me want to cry.

494
00:35:35,510 --> 00:35:37,552
Say, are you applying
to any colleges?

495
00:35:37,553 --> 00:35:40,680
Yeah, I'm aiming for one in Tokyo.

496
00:35:40,681 --> 00:35:42,265
Tokyo?

497
00:35:42,266 --> 00:35:43,475
I see...

498
00:35:43,476 --> 00:35:44,936
I'm not surprised.

499
00:35:45,853 --> 00:35:46,895
Why's that?

500
00:35:46,896 --> 00:35:49,857
You just look like you're
dying to get out of here.

501
00:35:50,775 --> 00:35:51,858
What about you?

502
00:35:51,859 --> 00:35:53,485
Well...

503
00:35:53,486 --> 00:35:56,738
I have no idea what tomorrow will hold.

504
00:35:56,739 --> 00:35:58,698
That's probably how
most people feel.

505
00:35:58,699 --> 00:35:59,492
Yeah right!

506
00:35:59,493 --> 00:36:00,575
You included?

507
00:36:00,576 --> 00:36:01,576
Of course.

508
00:36:02,411 --> 00:36:05,413
But you look like you've
got it all figured out.

509
00:36:05,414 --> 00:36:06,290
I wish.

510
00:36:06,291 --> 00:36:08,625
I spend all my time hesitating.

511
00:36:08,626 --> 00:36:11,002
I struggle to do the best I can.

512
00:36:11,003 --> 00:36:12,003
No time to relax.

513
00:36:12,797 --> 00:36:13,797
Really?

514
00:36:15,007 --> 00:36:16,425
I didn't know.

515
00:36:23,766 --> 00:36:24,850
A paper airplane?

516
00:36:24,851 --> 00:36:25,851
Yeah.

517
00:36:45,496 --> 00:36:48,040
Detour

518
00:37:10,813 --> 00:37:14,192
National Space Development Agency ofJapan

519
00:37:16,360 --> 00:37:17,528
Wow...

520
00:37:18,863 --> 00:37:20,530
I've heard it's 5 kilometers per hour.

521
00:37:20,531 --> 00:37:21,531
Huh?

522
00:37:22,408 --> 00:37:24,409
The speed at which it travels
to Minamitane's launch pad.

523
00:37:24,410 --> 00:37:25,410
Oh.

524
00:37:25,870 --> 00:37:28,788
They're going to launch one this
year for the first time in a while.

525
00:37:28,789 --> 00:37:32,500
I know. It's headed for the
edge of the solar system.

526
00:37:32,501 --> 00:37:33,711
The journey will take years.

527
00:37:53,397 --> 00:37:57,484
You should talk to Kanae
about her future.

528
00:37:57,485 --> 00:37:59,069
She can be so indecisive.

529
00:37:59,070 --> 00:38:00,403
She'll be fine.

530
00:38:00,404 --> 00:38:02,365
She's not a kid anymore.

531
00:38:06,452 --> 00:38:08,371
I used to be just like her.

532
00:38:10,456 --> 00:38:11,748
Guess what, Cub.

533
00:38:11,749 --> 00:38:13,751
Takaki doesn't know what
he wants to do either.

534
00:38:14,585 --> 00:38:17,046
He's just like me.

535
00:38:18,130 --> 00:38:24,303
It was a journey more lonely
than I could possibly imagine.

536
00:38:25,554 --> 00:38:28,932
Plunging headlong through
impenetrable darkness,

537
00:38:28,933 --> 00:38:32,311
with next to no chance of spotting
a single atom of hydrogen...

538
00:38:33,104 --> 00:38:38,484
A desperate search of the abyss,
for the secrets of this world...

539
00:38:44,115 --> 00:38:47,660
How far will we go in search
of those answers?

540
00:38:48,536 --> 00:38:50,746
How far are we able to?

541
00:39:01,173 --> 00:39:05,427
Subject: What I dreamt this morning
"I was walking through a field on
another planet with that same girl.
As usual, I couldn't see her face.
But it all felt very familiar."

542
00:39:05,428 --> 00:39:05,845
Save message?

543
00:39:05,846 --> 00:39:07,305
No

544
00:39:10,057 --> 00:39:14,478
When did I start writing messages
I could never send?

545
00:39:51,849 --> 00:39:54,267
Kanae, did you figure out
what you want to do?

546
00:39:54,268 --> 00:39:57,187
No, not yet.

547
00:39:57,188 --> 00:39:58,229
But it's okay.

548
00:39:58,230 --> 00:39:59,731
I've decided something.

549
00:39:59,732 --> 00:40:01,858
I'll just take everything
step-by-step.

550
00:40:01,859 --> 00:40:02,859
I'm off!

551
00:40:20,544 --> 00:40:24,714
After that day, a number
of typhoons passed by,

552
00:40:24,715 --> 00:40:27,802
and the island became
a little cooler each time.

553
00:40:30,137 --> 00:40:33,723
The wind rustling the sugarcane
fields became a little chillier.

554
00:40:33,724 --> 00:40:35,934
The sky felt a little higher.

555
00:40:35,935 --> 00:40:38,561
The outlines of the clouds were softer,

556
00:40:38,562 --> 00:40:42,775
and the students who rode their Cubs to
school began wearing light jackets.

557
00:40:58,624 --> 00:41:01,918
My first successful attempt
to ride a wave in six months...

558
00:41:01,919 --> 00:41:05,798
...came at the end of summer's warmth,
in the middle of October.

559
00:41:17,268 --> 00:41:22,021
This evening's forecast calls for sunny skies,
with winds of up to 8 meters per second.

560
00:41:22,022 --> 00:41:25,275
I heard Yamada asked Sasaki out.

561
00:41:25,276 --> 00:41:26,985
Wow.

562
00:41:26,986 --> 00:41:27,986
Huh?

563
00:41:27,987 --> 00:41:29,904
You seem happy today, Kanae.

564
00:41:29,905 --> 00:41:31,615
Finally make progress with Takaki?

565
00:41:32,199 --> 00:41:33,159
Hehe.

566
00:41:33,159 --> 00:41:33,951
No way!

567
00:41:33,952 --> 00:41:35,743
Make sure you remember this formula.

568
00:41:35,744 --> 00:41:37,120
Today's the day
It'll be on the final.

569
00:41:37,121 --> 00:41:39,957
I tell Takaki how I feel.

570
00:41:44,962 --> 00:41:47,172
If I can't do it on the day I rode a wave,

571
00:41:47,173 --> 00:41:50,176
then it's never going to happen.

572
00:42:00,686 --> 00:42:01,853
Kanae.

573
00:42:01,854 --> 00:42:02,854
Ta...

574
00:42:03,939 --> 00:42:05,398
Takaki...

575
00:42:05,399 --> 00:42:06,317
You heading home now?

576
00:42:06,318 --> 00:42:07,318
Yeah.

577
00:42:07,318 --> 00:42:08,277
I see.

578
00:42:08,278 --> 00:42:10,571
Let's go together.

579
00:42:33,219 --> 00:42:35,887
Oh? You made up your
mind pretty quick today.

580
00:42:35,888 --> 00:42:36,888
Yep.

581
00:42:44,146 --> 00:42:45,146
Um...

582
00:42:47,983 --> 00:42:48,983
What's wrong?

583
00:42:56,200 --> 00:42:57,492
...being so nice to me...

584
00:42:57,493 --> 00:42:58,493
Huh?

585
00:42:59,995 --> 00:43:01,329
Nothing...

586
00:43:01,330 --> 00:43:03,249
Sorry, forget it.

587
00:43:11,757 --> 00:43:12,924
Having trouble?

588
00:43:12,925 --> 00:43:13,884
Yeah.

589
00:43:13,884 --> 00:43:14,884
That's weird.

590
00:43:16,345 --> 00:43:17,263
No good?

591
00:43:17,264 --> 00:43:18,388
Yeah...

592
00:43:18,389 --> 00:43:20,890
The spark plug might be dead.

593
00:43:20,891 --> 00:43:21,975
Was this a hand-me-down?

594
00:43:21,976 --> 00:43:23,268
Yeah, it was my sister's.

595
00:43:23,269 --> 00:43:25,061
Did it sputter when you accelerated?

596
00:43:25,062 --> 00:43:26,105
It might have.

597
00:43:27,773 --> 00:43:29,816
You'll have to leave it here for now.

598
00:43:29,817 --> 00:43:32,193
Ask someone from your
family to pick it up later.

599
00:43:32,194 --> 00:43:33,403
I'll walk you home.

600
00:43:33,404 --> 00:43:34,363
What?

601
00:43:34,364 --> 00:43:36,030
I can walk by myself.

602
00:43:36,031 --> 00:43:38,032
You can go home.

603
00:43:38,033 --> 00:43:39,909
It's not that far from here.

604
00:43:39,910 --> 00:43:42,329
And I feel like walking anyway.

605
00:44:18,198 --> 00:44:19,532
Takaki...

606
00:44:19,533 --> 00:44:20,659
Please...

607
00:44:32,004 --> 00:44:33,046
What's wrong?

608
00:44:33,047 --> 00:44:34,047
I'm sorry...

609
00:44:34,882 --> 00:44:36,299
It's nothing...

610
00:44:36,300 --> 00:44:37,300
I'm sorry...

611
00:44:39,970 --> 00:44:40,970
Kanae?

612
00:44:43,057 --> 00:44:44,474
Please...

613
00:44:44,475 --> 00:44:46,727
Stop being...

614
00:44:47,561 --> 00:44:48,979
...so nice to me.

615
00:46:24,074 --> 00:46:28,077
We're so desperate to
reach beyond the clouds...

616
00:46:28,078 --> 00:46:31,080
...that we launched these
massive objects...

617
00:46:31,081 --> 00:46:34,376
...while we stared
off into the distance.

618
00:46:39,923 --> 00:46:43,384
I think that was when I realized...

619
00:46:43,385 --> 00:46:45,928
...what made Takaki different
from everybody else.

620
00:46:45,929 --> 00:46:48,181
And that was also when...

621
00:46:48,182 --> 00:46:51,100
...it became painfully clear...

622
00:46:51,101 --> 00:46:53,353
...that he didn't truly see me.

623
00:46:58,233 --> 00:47:02,321
That's why I couldn't bring myself
to tell him how I felt that day.

624
00:47:16,418 --> 00:47:19,003
Takaki was a good guy...

625
00:47:19,004 --> 00:47:20,547
An incredibly nice guy...

626
00:47:22,299 --> 00:47:27,053
But he was always looking
at something beyond me.

627
00:47:27,054 --> 00:47:29,348
Something very far away.

628
00:47:40,400 --> 00:47:44,612
Takaki would never
reciprocate my feelings.

629
00:47:44,613 --> 00:47:46,114
And yet...

630
00:47:46,615 --> 00:47:48,241
And yet I was certain that...

631
00:47:48,242 --> 00:47:52,036
...come tomorrow, the next day,
and every day after that,

632
00:47:52,037 --> 00:47:54,373
I wouldn't be able to keep
myself from loving him.

633
00:47:57,334 --> 00:48:00,419
And as I drowned in thoughts of him,

634
00:48:00,420 --> 00:48:03,340
I proceeded to cry myself to sleep.

635
00:48:03,590 --> 00:48:06,385
Episode 2 - Cosmonaut
End

636
