638
00:49:29,593 --> 00:49:31,761
I couldn't shake the feeling...

639
00:49:31,762 --> 00:49:35,766
...that if I were to turn around,
she would do the same.

640
00:49:49,613 --> 00:49:53,909
Today's last Chuo-Sobu line train
bound for Tokyo has arrived.

641
00:51:09,693 --> 00:51:11,736
You should stay until New Year's.

642
00:51:11,737 --> 00:51:12,820
I know.

643
00:51:12,821 --> 00:51:14,947
But I need to get everything ready.

644
00:51:14,948 --> 00:51:16,490
That's true.

645
00:51:16,491 --> 00:51:18,701
You should cook something
nice for him.

646
00:51:18,702 --> 00:51:19,536
I will.

647
00:51:19,537 --> 00:51:22,538
Let us know if anything
comes up, Akari.

648
00:51:22,539 --> 00:51:23,622
I'll be fine.

649
00:51:23,623 --> 00:51:25,708
We'll see each other at the
wedding next month,

650
00:51:25,709 --> 00:51:27,376
so you don't need
to worry so much.

651
00:51:27,377 --> 00:51:30,417
The train is approaching the platform 2.
It's cold out. You should head home.

652
00:51:50,484 --> 00:51:53,320
Last night, I had a dream
of days gone by.

653
00:51:54,696 --> 00:51:57,741
Of when he and I were still children.

654
00:51:58,658 --> 00:52:00,743
It was probably because of the letter

655
00:52:00,744 --> 00:52:02,104
Dear Takaki Tono
I found yesterday.

656
00:52:43,829 --> 00:52:50,001
"Hello, Takaki.
It's been a while. How are you?
After some thinking, I've decided
there's something I need to tell you."

657
00:52:52,045 --> 00:52:54,046
Ms. Takagi, could you process this for me?

658
00:52:54,047 --> 00:52:55,589
Message sent
Mr. Shirokai, you have a call on line two.

659
00:52:55,590 --> 00:52:56,424
Miss Mizuno.

660
00:52:56,425 --> 00:52:57,550
Ah, yes?

661
00:52:57,551 --> 00:52:58,717
Coming to the meeting?

662
00:52:58,718 --> 00:52:59,718
Yes.

663
00:53:08,311 --> 00:53:10,938
I was just going through
the motions of life.

664
00:53:10,939 --> 00:53:13,275
Sorrow was building
wherever I looked.

665
00:53:14,734 --> 00:53:16,569
On my bedsheets.

666
00:53:16,570 --> 00:53:18,612
On my toothbrush.

667
00:53:18,613 --> 00:53:20,699
In my cell phone history.

668
00:53:42,929 --> 00:53:45,307
"I still love you."

669
00:53:46,057 --> 00:53:49,644
Said a message from the woman I'd
been with for the past three years.

670
00:53:51,104 --> 00:53:55,816
"But after a thousand
message exchanges,

671
00:53:55,817 --> 00:54:00,280
our hearts have only grown
closer by 1 centimeter."

672
00:54:08,622 --> 00:54:10,289
For the past few years,

673
00:54:10,290 --> 00:54:12,041
I had been trying to move on.

674
00:54:12,042 --> 00:54:14,752
I was grasping for something
I couldn't reach.

675
00:54:14,753 --> 00:54:17,004
I didn't even know what it was.

676
00:54:17,005 --> 00:54:20,382
Not knowing the root
of these violent feelings,

677
00:54:20,383 --> 00:54:23,887
I could only slave away at my work.

678
00:54:24,638 --> 00:54:25,555
The next thing I knew,

679
00:54:25,556 --> 00:54:28,808
I felt the pain of watching
my heart go numb.

680
00:54:30,852 --> 00:54:32,853
One morning,

681
00:54:32,854 --> 00:54:35,981
I discovered that I had completely lost...

682
00:54:35,982 --> 00:54:38,652
...those sincere feelings I once had.

683
00:54:39,361 --> 00:54:41,654
I reached the end of my rope...

684
00:54:41,655 --> 00:54:43,240
...and quit my job.

685
00:55:09,391 --> 00:55:11,725
Last night, I had a dream.

686
00:55:11,726 --> 00:55:13,520
A dream of days gone by.

687
00:55:14,354 --> 00:55:17,857
In the dream, we were
still thirteen years old.

688
00:55:18,358 --> 00:55:22,736
We were in the middle of a
large field blanketed by snow.

689
00:55:22,737 --> 00:55:26,949
Faint artificial light shined
from houses in the distance.

690
00:55:26,950 --> 00:55:31,955
"Japan's Deep Space Exploration Probe Elish
Finally Exits Solar System"
Our footprints were all that
blemished the virgin snow.

691
00:55:32,539 --> 00:55:33,872
And...

692
00:55:33,873 --> 00:55:37,501
We believed we would one day watch
the cherry blossoms together again.

693
00:55:37,502 --> 00:55:40,921
Of that, we had no doubt.

694
00:55:40,922 --> 00:55:42,716
Of that, we were certain.

695
00:55:43,132 --> 00:55:50,138
5 <i>Centimeters Per Second
Everywhere I go, I look for you.</i>

696
00:55:50,139 --> 00:55:52,057
<i>I look on platforms,</i>

697
00:55:52,058 --> 00:55:53,975
<i>and in windows from alleys.</i>

698
00:55:53,976 --> 00:55:57,979
<i>Knowing I'll never find you there.</i>

699
00:55:57,980 --> 00:56:01,274
<i>If my wish comes true,</i>

700
00:56:01,275 --> 00:56:04,861
<i>I'd go straight to you.</i>

701
00:56:04,862 --> 00:56:08,698
<i>I'd do everything I ever wanted to do.</i>

702
00:56:08,699 --> 00:56:14,914
<i>I'd hold you with all the power
I have gained in my life.</i>

703
00:56:23,840 --> 00:56:28,803
<i>Anybody can help me forget my loneliness.</i>

704
00:56:31,305 --> 00:56:34,684
<i>But it has to be you...</i>

705
00:56:35,685 --> 00:56:38,395
<i>...because the stars are so bright.</i>

706
00:56:38,396 --> 00:56:40,690
<i>One more time.</i>

707
00:56:41,691 --> 00:56:46,069
<i>I pray for the seasons to stand still.</i>

708
00:56:46,070 --> 00:56:47,989
<i>One more time.</i>

709
00:56:48,865 --> 00:56:53,285
<i>I want to go back to those carefree days.</i>

710
00:56:53,286 --> 00:57:00,876
<i>Everywhere I go, I look for you.</i>

711
00:57:00,877 --> 00:57:02,711
<i>At the intersection.</i>

712
00:57:02,712 --> 00:57:04,588
<i>In my dreams every night.</i>

713
00:57:04,589 --> 00:57:08,216
<i>Knowing I'd never find you there.</i>

714
00:57:08,217 --> 00:57:11,928
<i>If I could perform a miracle,</i>

715
00:57:11,929 --> 00:57:15,307
<i>I would show you how...</i>

716
00:57:15,308 --> 00:57:19,102
...I <i>am different now,
on this new morning.</i>

717
00:57:19,103 --> 00:57:25,109
<i>I'd tell you "I love you,"
though I never could before.</i>

718
00:57:34,243 --> 00:57:38,623
<i>Memories of summer
spin round and round.</i>

719
00:57:42,209 --> 00:57:48,007
<i>I</i> can't even hear <i>my</i> heartbeat.

720
00:57:49,175 --> 00:57:56,932
<i>Everywhere I go, I look for you.</i>

721
00:57:56,933 --> 00:57:58,725
<i>Every morning.</i>

722
00:57:58,726 --> 00:58:00,393
<i>In the town of Sakuragi-Cho.</i>

723
00:58:00,394 --> 00:58:04,314
<i>Knowing I'd never find you there.</i>

724
00:58:04,315 --> 00:58:08,151
<i>If my wish comes true,</i>

725
00:58:08,152 --> 00:58:11,696
<i>I'd go straight to you.</i>

726
00:58:11,697 --> 00:58:15,158
<i>I'd do everything I'd ever wanted to do.</i>

727
00:58:15,159 --> 00:58:19,037
<i>I'd hold you with all the power
I have gained in my life.</i>

728
00:58:19,038 --> 00:58:23,960
<i>I always look for signs of you.</i>

729
00:58:26,170 --> 00:58:27,921
<i>In the shops on my travels.</i>

730
00:58:27,922 --> 00:58:29,881
<i>Even in newspaper columns.</i>

731
00:58:29,882 --> 00:58:33,468
<i>Knowing I'd never find you there.</i>

732
00:58:33,469 --> 00:58:37,180
<i>If I could perform a miracle,</i>

733
00:58:37,181 --> 00:58:40,809
<i>I would show you how...</i>

734
00:58:40,810 --> 00:58:44,229
...I <i>am different now,
on</i> a <i>new morning.</i>

735
00:58:44,230 --> 00:58:48,149
<i>I'd tell you "I love you,"
though I never could before.</i>

736
00:58:48,150 --> 00:58:55,365
<i>Everywhere I look,
I always look for your smile.</i>

737
00:58:55,366 --> 00:58:57,158
<i>At the crossing,</i>

738
00:58:57,159 --> 00:58:59,035
<i>waiting for the trains to pass.</i>

739
00:58:59,036 --> 00:59:02,414
<i>Knowing I'll never find you there.</i>

740
00:59:02,415 --> 00:59:06,459
<i>If I were born again,</i>

741
00:59:06,460 --> 00:59:10,046
<i>I'd come to you.</i>

742
00:59:10,047 --> 00:59:13,925
<i>For there's nothing I want in this world...</i>

743
00:59:13,926 --> 00:59:20,766
<i>...besides your love.
Nothing else matters.</i>

744
01:02:38,339 --> 01:02:43,677
The End

